replyContent: Hi David, to change Navigation methods: 1) Start your Tecarta Bible app 2) Tap the center navigation drawer that has a Book name and Chapter number 3) You will see a navigation method appear 4) On the top of the screen you will see a little gear icon. Tap this icon to see a navigation menu appear 5) Select either Wheel, 3-Tap, 2-Tap, or Keyboard

replyContent: There are several ways to navigate. Here's how to pick one of the methods: 1) Start the app 2) Tap the center navigation drawer [Book name & Chapter number] 3) On the top of the screen you will see a little gear icon. replyContent:
Sorry you're experiencing problems. I'm afraid that there has been some confusion :(
A pinch-zoom feature was never incorporated in any version of the Tecarta Bible. If you are trying to increase the font size, simply tap the My Library drawer (book icon), go to Settings, and then adjust the font under Font Size. :)

replyContent:
Hi Gene,
Sorry you're experiencing problems :(
1. Please go to Settings on your Device
2. Select Language and Keyboard
3. Select Text-to-Speech Output/Voice Input and Output
4. Under Preferred Engine, please make sure that you are using Google's default Text-to-Speech Engine. If the data is not installed, install the data
